parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front spring perch can cause the coil spring to eject, potentially puncturing the front tire, leading to loss of control, accidents, and possible fatalities.
symptoms: coil spring rolls across the road
rust or corrosion at the weld points of the upper constraint for the front coil spring.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Spring Perch Failure Due to Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front spring perch due to rust can cause the front of the vehicle to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries.
symptoms: The front of the vehicle falls down onto the wheel
right front wheel leaps into the air
underside of the front end of the vehicle drops to the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lower Control Arm Failure Due to Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower control arm can cause loss of vehicle control, potentially leading to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel no longer lines up straight
rubbing or whining noise from the front left
cracked and bent lower control arm
